    <div class="container">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <h2 style="border: none; text-align: center; color: #666; margin-top: 0;">Phasmophobia Companion</h2>

        <div class="meta-info">
            <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> November 3, 2025</p>
            <p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> November 3, 2025</p>
            <p><span class="status-badge">ACTIVE</span></p>
        </div>

        <!-- Introduction -->
        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>
            Phasmophobia Companion ("App", "we", "us", or "our") operates the Phasmophobia Companion mobile application. This Privacy Policy explains our practices regarding data collection, use, and protection when you use our App.
        </p>
        <p>
            This Privacy Policy applies to our App and explains our data practices. If you do not agree with our policies and practices, please do not use our App.
        </p>

        <hr>

        <!-- Information We Collect -->
        <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>

        <h3>2.1 Information You Provide Directly</h3>

        <h4>Account & Authentication:</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>We do not require user accounts or authentication</li>
            <li>No personal information (name, email, phone number) is collected</li>
            <li>No login credentials are stored</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>In-App Purchases:</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>When you purchase premium features via in-app purchase, transaction data is handled by Apple App Store (iOS) or Google Play Store (Android)</li>
            <li>We store locally on your device:
                <ul>
                    <li>Premium status (yes/no)</li>
                    <li>Purchase date</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>These are stored in encrypted local storage (AsyncStorage) on your device only</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>Bookmarks & Custom Data:</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>Ghost bookmarks, equipment presets, and notes you create are stored locally on your device</li>
            <li>This data is not sent to our servers</li>
            <li>You can export or delete this data anytime through the app settings</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2.2 Automatically Collected Information</h3>

        <h4>Advertising Data:</h4>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Google Mobile Ads (AdMob):</strong> When ads are displayed, Google collects:
                <ul>
                    <li>Ad impressions and interactions</li>
                    <li>Approximate location (based on IP)</li>
                    <li>Device identifiers (advertising ID)</li>
                    <li>App usage data related to ad serving</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Ad Revenue:</strong> We receive aggregate (non-personal) ad revenue data</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>App Analytics:</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>We do not currently use Firebase Analytics or third-party analytics</li>
            <li>Crash reporting: Not currently implemented (coming soon)</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>Device Information:</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>Device type and OS version (for app compatibility)</li>
            <li>Platform (iOS or Android)</li>
            <li>This is used to ensure the app functions properly</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>Logs:</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>Console logs for debugging (not sent anywhere)</li>
            <li>Stored locally on your device only</li>
        </ul>

        <hr>

        <!-- How We Use Information -->
        <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use collected information for:</p>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>Service Provision</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Delivering premium features after purchase</li>
                    <li>Managing your local bookmarks and data</li>
                    <li>Improving app stability and performance</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Advertising</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Serving relevant ads through Google Mobile Ads (AdMob)</li>
                    <li>Measuring ad performance and user engagement</li>
                    <li>Optimizing ad delivery and fill rates</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Fraud Prevention</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Detecting and preventing fraudulent in-app purchases</li>
                    <li>Monitoring for suspicious activity</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Legal Compliance</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Complying with applicable laws and regulations</li>
                    <li>Responding to legal requests from authorities</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Product Improvement</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Understanding how users interact with features</li>
                    <li>Fixing bugs and improving performance</li>
                    <li>Planning future features</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ol>

        <hr>

        <!-- Information Sharing & Disclosure -->
        <h2>4. Information Sharing & Disclosure</h2>

        <h3>4.1 Third-Party Services</h3>

        <h4>Google Mobile Ads (AdMob)</h4>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Displaying advertisements</li>
            <li><strong>Data Shared:</strong> Device advertising ID, approximate location, app usage</li>
            <li><strong>Privacy Policy:</strong> <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">Google Privacy Policy</a></li>
        </ul>

        <h4>Apple App Store / Google Play Store</h4>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> In-app purchase processing</li>
            <li><strong>Data Shared:</strong> Purchase information, billing address (if provided by you)</li>
            <li><strong>Privacy Policies:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li><a href="https://www.apple.com/privacy/" target="_blank">Apple Privacy Policy</a></li>
                    <li><a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">Google Privacy Policy</a></li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h4>React Native & Expo</h4>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> App development framework</li>
            <li>No personal data is shared with these platforms</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>4.2 Legal Requirements</h3>
        <p>We may disclose your information when required by law:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Court orders</li>
            <li>Government investigations</li>
            <li>Law enforcement requests</li>
            <li>Protection of rights and safety</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>4.3 Business Transfers</h3>
        <p>
            If our company is acquired or merged, your information may be transferred as part of that transaction. We will notify you of any such change and any choices you may have regarding your information.
        </p>

        <h3>4.4 No Selling of Data</h3>
        <div class="highlight">
            <strong>We do NOT sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties.</strong>
        </div>

        <hr>

        <!-- Data Retention -->
        <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>

        <h3>Local Device Data:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Bookmarks, presets, and preferences: Stored until you delete them</li>
            <li>Premium status: Stored while app is installed</li>
            <li>Purchasing data: Stored for account recovery and restore purposes</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Server Data:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>No personal data is stored on our servers</li>
            <li>Ad performance data (aggregate only) retained per Google's policy</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Deletion:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Uninstalling the app will delete all local data</li>
            <li>You can manually clear app data through device settings</li>
            <li>Request to delete account/data is not applicable (no accounts exist)</li>
        </ul>

        <hr>

        <!-- Data Security -->
        <h2>6. Data Security</h2>

        <h3>6.1 Security Measures</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Local data is encrypted using AsyncStorage (React Native encrypted storage)</li>
            <li>In-app purchase data is handled securely by Apple/Google</li>
            <li>No data transmission over unencrypted connections</li>
            <li>HTTPS for any future server communications</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>6.2 Limitations</h3>
        <p>
            While we implement industry-standard security measures, no system is 100% secure. We cannot guarantee absolute security. Users are responsible for maintaining device security (lock screens, passwords, etc.).
        </p>

        <hr>

        <!-- Children's Privacy -->
        <h2>7. Children's Privacy (COPPA Compliance)</h2>

        <h3>United States (COPPA - Children's Online Privacy Protection Act):</h3>
        <p>
            Our App is not directed to children under 13 years old. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we become aware that a child under 13 has provided us with personal information, we will delete such information immediately and terminate the child's account.
        </p>

        <h3>European Union (GDPR - Children):</h3>
        <p>
            For users under 16 years old, parental consent is required for data processing. However, since we collect minimal personal data, this mostly applies to ad targeting through Google.
        </p>

        <h3>Rest of World:</h3>
        <p>
            Parents or guardians concerned about data collection should review this privacy policy and monitor their children's app usage.
        </p>

        <hr>

        <!-- Your Privacy Rights -->
        <h2>8. Your Privacy Rights</h2>

        <h3>8.1 United States (California - CCPA/CPRA)</h3>
        <p>You have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Know what personal information is collected</li>
            <li>Delete personal information</li>
            <li>Opt-out of data sales (we don't sell data anyway)</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>California Residents:</strong> Contact us if you wish to exercise these rights.</p>

        <h3>8.2 European Union (GDPR)</h3>
        <p>You have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Access your personal data</li>
            <li>Correct inaccurate data</li>
            <li>Delete your data ("right to be forgotten")</li>
            <li>Restrict processing</li>
            <li>Data portability</li>
            <li>Object to processing</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>EU Residents:</strong> Contact us to exercise these rights. We will respond within 30 days.</p>

        <h3>8.3 Canada (PIPEDA)</h3>
        <p>You have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Access your personal information</li>
            <li>Request corrections</li>
            <li>Opt-out of marketing communications</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>8.4 Advertising Preferences</h3>
        <p><strong>Reset Advertising ID (opt out of personalized ads):</strong></p>

        <h4>iOS:</h4>
        <div class="code-block">
            Settings → Privacy → Apple Advertising<br>
            Tap "Personalized Ads" to toggle off
        </div>

        <h4>Android:</h4>
        <div class="code-block">
            Google Settings → Manage your Google Account<br>
            Privacy & Security → Advertising settings<br>
            Manage Your Google Ads settings
        </div>

        <hr>

        <!-- Cookie Policy -->
        <h2>9. Cookie Policy</h2>
        <p>Our App does not use traditional cookies. However:</p>

        <ul>
            <li><strong>Local Storage:</strong> We use local app storage (AsyncStorage) to remember:
                <ul>
                    <li>Your premium status</li>
                    <li>Bookmarks and preferences</li>
                    <li>App settings</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Advertising Cookies:</strong> Google Mobile Ads may use persistent identifiers similar to cookies for ad targeting. See Google's Privacy Policy for details.</li>
        </ul>

        <hr>

        <!-- Third-Party Links -->
        <h2>10. Third-Party Links</h2>
        <p>
            Our App may contain links to external websites and services (Phasmophobia Wiki, game guides, etc.). This Privacy Policy does not apply to third-party sites. We are not responsible for their privacy practices.
        </p>
        <p>
            When you access third-party links, you are subject to their privacy policies.
        </p>

        <hr>

        <!-- International Data Transfers -->
        <h2>11. International Data Transfers</h2>
        <p>
            Our App is available globally. Your information may be transferred to, stored in, and processed in countries other than your country of residence. These countries may have different data protection laws.
        </p>
        <p>
            By using our App, you consent to such transfers. We ensure transfers comply with applicable laws including GDPR, CCPA, and others.
        </p>

        <hr>

        <!-- Contact Us -->
        <h2>12. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or our privacy practices, please contact us:</p>

        <div class="highlight">
            <p><strong>Email:</strong> karmaplayzz2002@gmail.com</p>
            <p><strong>Response Time:</strong> We will respond to privacy inquiries within 30 days.</p>
        </div>

        <hr>

        <!-- Policy Changes -->
        <h2>13. Policy Changes</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of material changes by:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Updating the "Last Updated" date</li>
            <li>Posting the new policy in the App</li>
            <li>Requesting your consent if required by law</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            Your continued use of the App after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated Privacy Policy.
        </p>

        <hr>

        <!-- Additional Information by Region -->
